Subject: [PATCH] fix(shizuku): comprehensive Shizuku integration fix per
 official API
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

6 critical Shizuku integration bugs fixed after studying official
Shizuku developer guide (https://github.com/RikkaApps/Shizuku):

BUG 1 (CRITICAL): destroy() must call System.exit(0)
Per Shizuku API docs: 'In this method, you can do some cleanup jobs
and call System.exit() in the end.' System.exit(0) is REQUIRED to
properly terminate the user service process. The previous fix removed
it, which prevented Shizuku from properly managing the service lifecycle.
The real issue was handleOnDestroy() calling destroy() at the wrong
time — that was already fixed. Now destroy() correctly calls
System.exit(0) as required by Shizuku API.

BUG 2 (CRITICAL): ShizukuPlugin.kt conflicts with TouchInjectionPlugin
Both plugins registered Shizuku.addRequestPermissionResultListener,
causing duplicate permission callbacks. ShizukuPlugin also bound a
SECOND user service with DIFFERENT UserServiceArgs (no tag, no version,
no processNameSuffix). Additionally, ShizukuPlugin used
IGamepadDaemonService.Stub.asInterface() but TouchDaemonService
implements ITouchService.Stub — type mismatch.
Fix: Deleted ShizukuPlugin.kt and IGamepadDaemonService.aidl entirely.
TouchInjectionPlugin already handles all Shizuku operations.
Removed ShizukuPlugin registration from MainActivity.

BUG 3 (HIGH): No tag on UserServiceArgs
Per Shizuku API docs: 'Shizuku uses tag from UserServiceArgs to
determine if the User Service is same. If tag is not set, class name
will be used, but class name is unstable after ProGuard/R8.'
Fix: Added .tag('touch_daemon_v1') to UserServiceArgs.

BUG 4 (HIGH): No isPreV11() check
Per Shizuku API docs: 'if (Shizuku.isPreV11()) { return false; }'
should be checked before any Shizuku API call. Pre-v11 is unsupported.
Fix: Added isPreV11() check in bindService(), requestPermission(),
and checkPermission().

BUG 5 (MEDIUM): No pingBinder() check before bindService
bindService was called without checking if Shizuku binder is active.
Fix: Added Shizuku.pingBinder() check before attempting to bind.
If binder is not active, return clear error message.

BUG 6 (MEDIUM): No pingBinder() in checkPermission
checkPermission used Shizuku.pingBinder() but didn't check isPreV11.
Fix: Added comprehensive checks in checkPermission.
